    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Chargé in Syria (
                        Memminger
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1947v05</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d818</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">818</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1947-10-11T06:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1947-10-11T06:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-10-11T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-10-11T06:00:00-05:00" n="818" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d818">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/10–1147: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Syria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Memminger</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Damascus</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-11T13:00:00+02:00">October 11, 1947—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>325. Syrian army units from Horns, Hama, Aleppo as well as Damascus moving slowly
                    orderly to Palestine frontier today. (Reference Legation’s telegram 323, October
                        10<note n="1" xml:id="d818fn1">Not printed.</note>). Visit Damascus area
                    camps this morning revealed loaded convoys and men awaiting march order.</p>
                <p>Damascus press predicts early declaration independent Palestine [and] formation
                    Arab Government under presidency Grand Mufti; <pb facs="1194" n="1180" xml:id="pg_1180"/> claims this decision taken in addition those published
                    League’s formal communiqué.</p>
                <p>Sent Department as 325, repeated Beirut 14, Baghdad 36, London 17.</p>
                <p>Department please pass Jerusalem.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Memminger</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
